			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Epic is always worth getting, for status, looks, a feeling of accompishment!
<br />

<br />
Epic pet, as it stands, is better then all 61-65 pets if it can land it's proc for DPS. If it can, it's a machine, insane, god-like. 
<br />

<br />
Epic is also amazing at farming areas, with a solid DS, a good hit, awesome proc, and good hp/ac. 
<br />

<br />
Generally speaking each pet has their uses, as does epic:
<br />

<br />
Earth: When you need it's root, when you have a healer (low ac, but many hp means heal intervals are regular), yo yo kiting, pet chaining.
<br />
Water: When you can get to the mob's back often, for pure DPS, when you can't afford much push.
<br />
Air: When push is OK, when positioning is bad so you can't get to the back for DPS, when you want a stun, a good tank for many occasions.
<br />
Fire: When you need a laugh, extremely rare other occasions as is...
<br />

<br />
Epic: When it can land it's proc and you want DPS, when you are farming low blues or lower.
<br />

<br />
Epic is another option, about as powerful as other pets in some circumstances, less in some, more in others. It's a pet like any other, with it's own set of solid uses. It's no longer the be-all end-all of mage life however.<br />_________________<br />"The ability to quote is a serviceable substitute for wit."
<br />
-- George Bernard Shaw (1856 - 1950)
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/index.php">[65 Arch Convoker]</a> <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=399091" target="blank"><span style="font-weight: bold">Istaril</span></A> &lt;<a href="http://www.waster.net/wudan/">Wudan</a>&gt;</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
