			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There has been a lot of discussion about it and the concensus seems to be that if the Epic can land its procs/spells on the mob, it is generally superior to the PoP pets. Many, if not most Epic-ed mages use the Epic in pre-PoP zones as well as up through LDoN 65 Regular.
<br />

<br />
There are those that believe that the aggro generated by the Epic, even when the procs/spells don't land provides advantages over the PoP pets.
<br />

<br />
One downside of the Epic pet is its low level. It will attract adds more readily than the PoP pets.
<br />

<br />
Is it worth getting in my opinion? YES.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568700" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
