			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As a recent Epic owner:
<br />

<br />
Pet is a beast. Even in PoStorms, his procs (both innate and weapon) land from time to time, and he hits for 81 (no DPoC yet) quite often. He cannot really tank for long, but can generally stand toe-to-toe with a LDoN lv60 mob with a little healing help from my part.
<br />

<br />
With the LDoN focus, I heard he becomes equal (situationnally) with he others PoP pets, and gains awesome regen (273HP per tic). His only real drawback is his lower level. But I am not yet at the point where it becomes a problem.
<br />

<br />
It's a very very nice tool to add to your belt, as was stated by Istaril. And, as a plus side, most of the quest items can now be soloed by an intelligent Mage. Only the Crown can be a problem, and it is purchasable...
<br />

<br />
Is it worth getting in my opinion? YES.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.legion-whiterose.com" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.legion-whiterose.com/signatures/legionnaires/loralon.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />
